{"name":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"villager","isMainNPC":false,"oppositionLevel":3,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I'm a thug always looking to fill my pockets with coin, no matter how dirty the job."],"agenda":["Collect the money I have hidden in the catacombs and flee far from Paris before the fire spirit finds me"],"gifts":[],"background":"A barely eighteen-year-old boy who works for Father Adrien as part of the Ravens, smugglers who transport absinthe through the catacombs. Olivier witnessed Adrien murder Yvonne but stayed silent. Now Yvonne's spirit is hunting him - his companion Thierry has already been burnt alive. Olivier confided in Adrien but realized the priest would do nothing to help him. Now desperately trying to collect his hidden money and leave the city before nightfall. If found before sunset, will be preparing his escape at the Ravens' Hideout. If not found in time, his charred corpse will be discovered after 10pm.","notes":"Time-sensitive NPC - must be found before nightfall to save him. Will reveal the truth about Yvonne's death if put under pressure. Knows about Adrien's absinthe operation and connection to the Ravens.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"The Smile in the Darkness","inspiration":"The Little Match Girl (Hans Christian Andersen)","role":"Victim - Witness"},"_id":"81bac32d4ee13fbd"}
{"name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"villager","isMainNPC":false,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to detail is obsessive."],"agenda":["Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée from prying eyes"],"gifts":[],"background":"An Italian doctor hired by the city of Paris to manage the Cemetery of the Innocents and the excessive number of corpses in the mass graves. Also a skilled astrologer. Lorenzo sent the cemetery keepers away claiming he needs quiet for his studies, but actually to secretly host Alizée, a nun he has fallen in love with. Knows about the passage of comet Morituris and how it gives power to spirits. Plans to wait until the new year to embark with Alizée towards the New World. Will appear nervous and keep looking over his shoulder at Alizée's hiding spot.","notes":"Potential ally if Hunters are discreet about Alizée. Can provide information about spirits, the comet, and the dangerous state of the mass graves. Has keys to access the underground pit.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"The Smile in the Darkness","inspiration":"The Little Match Girl (Hans Christian Andersen)","role":"Supporting Character - Doctor/Astrologer"},"_id":"875d219c549f2be4"}
{"name":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"villager","isMainNPC":false,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability sometimes scares me."],"agenda":["Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don't need to fear the Church's punishment"],"gifts":[{"name":"Spiritualist","description":"Alizée can see and communicate with spirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past twenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit energy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can obtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she has perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove a Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits."}],"background":"A young nun who abandoned her religious vows for love of Lorenzo. Possesses the natural ability to see and communicate with spirits, though this gift sometimes frightens her. Hiding in the Cemetery of the Innocents to avoid the Church's severe judgment. Watches the Hunters from behind tombstones, ready to intervene to help Lorenzo. Will try not to reveal her abilities unless cornered. Can sense that spirits are very agitated due to both a powerful hateful spirit (Yvonne) and the imminent passage of the comet Morituris.","notes":"Key to resolving the spirit problem. Her Spiritualist Gift can remove Grudge Tokens from the underground pit. Will help if Hunters protect her and Lorenzo's secret.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"The Smile in the Darkness","inspiration":"The Little Match Girl (Hans Christian Andersen)","role":"Supporting Character - Spiritualist"},"_id":"fbcb508475c3eb18"}
